{"version":"0.3.1","markups":[],"atoms":[],"cards":[["card-markdown",{"cardName":"card-markdown","markdown":"I’m currently in the Dolomites. Do you know where the [Dolomites](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dolomites) are? I’m racing a 120km ultra race (74 miles) from Cortina, Italy. The race starts at 11pm. It’s going to be really hard. But it’s a privilege I’ll be quick to smile for, even when I feel like a sack of decaying milk cartons.

Also, I just finished a [Patagonia film tour](http://www.patagonia.com/new-localism/takayna.html), showing the documentary *takayna*. It’s about the *takayna*/Tarkine forest in Tasmania, which is outrageously valuable, but also currently being logged unsustainably and even illegally. [READ ABOUT IT and consider signing the change.org petition to make takayna a World Heritage Site.](http://www.patagonia.com/new-localism/takayna.html)

